Problem: 5.3-15. Three drugs are being tested for use as the treatment of a certain disease. Let $p_1, p_2$, and $p_3$ represent the probabilities of success for the respective drugs. As three patients come in, each is given one of the drugs in a random order. After $n=10$ "triples" and assuming independence, compute the probability that the maximum number of successes with one of the drugs exceeds eight if, in fact, $p_1=p_2=p_3=0.7$
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires finding the probability that the maximum number of successes with one of the three drugs exceeds eight, given that each drug has a success probability of 0.7 and is tested 10 times over 10 triples, with independence.

Each drug's number of successes follows a binomial distribution with \(n = 10\) trials and success probability \(p = 0.7\). The probability that the maximum number of successes exceeds eight is equivalent to the probability that at least one drug has more than eight successes (i.e., 9 or 10 successes).

The probability that a single drug has more than eight successes is:
\[
P(S_i > 8) = P(S_i = 9) + P(S_i = 10)
\]
where:
\[
P(S_i = 10) = (0.7)^{10} = 0.0282475249
\]
\[
P(S_i = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3)^1 = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3 = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821
\]
\[
P(S_i > 8) = 0.121060821 + 0.0282475249 = 0.1493083459
\]

Using the inclusion-exclusion principle for the three drugs:
\[
P(\text{max} > 8) = 3 \times P(S_i > 8) - 3 \times [P(S_i > 8)]^2 + [P(S_i > 8)]^3
\]
First, compute:
\[
[P(S_i > 8)]^2 = (0.1493083459)^2 = 0.02229298208574
\]
\[
[P(S_i > 8)]^3 = (0.1493083459)^3 = 0.02229298208574 \times 0.1493083459 = 0.0033283422254
\]
Then:
\[
3 \times P(S_i > 8) = 3 \times 0.1493083459 = 0.4479250377
\]
\[
3 \times [P(S_i > 8)]^2 = 3 \times 0.02229298208574 = 0.06687894625722
\]
\[
P(\text{max} > 8) = 0.4479250377 - 0.06687894625722 + 0.0033283422254 = 0.38437443366818
\]

Rounded to three significant figures, the probability is 0.384.

Summary: The final answer is $0.384$
