- First, compute \(h c = (6.626 \times 10^{-34}) \times (3.00 \times 10^8) = 1.9878 \times 10^{-25} \, \text{J·m}\).
- Then, energy per photon \(E_{\text{photon}} = \frac{1.9878 \times 10^{-25}}{3.00 \times 10^{-7}} = 6.626 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J}\).
